# Agent roster (fixed)

Do **not** keep adding Agent classes or numbered forks.

Forbidden examples: `ArchitectureAgent2`, `VisualAgent3`, `LayoutAgent4`,
`ResearchAgent`, `LayoutAgent`, `RenderAgent`, `CriticAgent`.

## Allowed product roles (exactly these six)

| Role | Responsibility (one line) |
|------|---------------------------|
| **Research** | Facts, sources, citations — not rhetoric |
| **Planning** | Mission / deliverables / workstreams — not slide geometry |
| **Narrative** | Outline, storyline, page intent / `SlideSpec` |
| **Visual** | Intent, composition, layout, grammar, image treatment (services) |
| **Render** | Execute approved scene → PPTX/PDF/PNG (no re-planning) |
| **Critic** | Actionable findings only — does not silently rewrite the deck |

## Implementation rule

- Prefer **Service + Domain artifact + Workflow node**.
- `archium/agents/` may hold a few LLM *planners* under Narrative/Research;
  new capability belongs in an existing role’s services, not a new Agent.
- Internal stages (Architecture schema, Composition, Layout) are **sub-steps of Visual**, not new Agents.

Canonical doc: `docs/architecture/pipeline-roles.md`.
